    }
  },
  {
    "content_id": 20013,
    "reference_id": 19181,
    "title": "Lamentations 1:8–9",
    "media_type": "Text",
    "index_reference": "25001008-25001009",
    "language": "eng",
    "content": "<p>Jerusalem was stripped of everything of physical and spiritual value that the people cherished.</p>",
    "associations": {
      "passage": [
        {
          "start_ref": "25001008",
          "start_ref_usfm": "LAM 1:8",
          "end_ref": "25001009",
          "end_ref_usfm": "LAM 1:9"
        }
      ],
      "resource": []
    }
  },
  {
    "content_id": 20001,
    "reference_id": 19169,
    "title": "Lamentations 1:10",
    "media_type": "Text",
    "index_reference": "25001010",
    "language": "eng",
    "content": "<p>For historical accounts of these events, see <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Kgs25:8-2Kgs25:17\">2&nbsp;Kgs 25:8–17</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Chr36:13-2Chr36:21\">2&nbsp;Chr 36:13–21</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer52:4-Jer52:30\">Jer 52:4–30</a>.</p>",
    "associations": {
      "passage": [
        {
          "start_ref": "25001010",
          "start_ref_usfm": "LAM 1:10",
          "end_ref": "25001010",
          "end_ref_usfm": "LAM 1:10"
        }
      ],
      "resource": []
    }
  },
  {
    "content_id": 20002,
    "reference_id": 19170,
    "title": "Lamentations 1:13",
    "media_type": "Text",
    "index_reference": "25001013",
    "language": "eng",
    "content": "<p>The destruction of Jerusalem at the hands of the Babylonians was like fire from heaven.</p>",
    "associations": {
      "passage": [
        {
          "start_ref": "25001013",
          "start_ref_usfm": "LAM 1:13",
          "end_ref": "25001013",
          "end_ref_usfm": "LAM 1:13"
        }
      ],
      "resource": []
    }
  },
  {
    "content_id": 20003,
    "reference_id": 19171,
    "title": "Lamentations 1:14",
    "media_type": "Text",
    "index_reference": "25001014",
    "language": "eng",
    "content": "<p>For their sins, the people of Judah were tied to one another with ropes and taken as captives into exile.</p>",
    "associations": {
      "passage": [
        {
          "start_ref": "25001014",
          "start_ref_usfm": "LAM 1:14",
          "end_ref": "25001014",
          "end_ref_usfm": "LAM 1:14"
        }
      ],
      "resource": []
    }
  },
  {
    "content_id": 20004,
    "reference_id": 19172,
    "title": "Lamentations 1:15",
    "media_type": "Text",
    "index_reference": "25001015",
    "language": "eng",
    "content": "<p>his beloved city: God had given special care to Jerusalem, like a father protecting his daughter. But her sins had been persistent, and her punishment was horrible. •&nbsp;like grapes .&nbsp;.&nbsp;. trampled in a winepress: This common procedure for extracting juice from grapes is used vividly in <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa63:3\">Isa 63:3</a> to show the horrors of punishment. In <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rev14:18-Rev14:20\">Rev 14:18–20</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rev19:15\">19:15</a>, the image graphically represents universal judgment.</p>",
    "associations": {
      "passage": [
        {
          "start_ref": "25001015",
          "start_ref_usfm": "LAM 1:15",
          "end_ref": "25001015",
          "end_ref_usfm": "LAM 1:15"
        }
      ],
      "resource": []
    }
  },
  {
    "content_id": 20005,
    "reference_id": 19173,
    "title": "Lamentations 1:19",
    "media_type": "Text",
    "index_reference": "25001019",
    "language": "eng",
    "content": "<p>I begged my allies: Egypt had a great deal of interest in Judah because Judah controlled the only good route to&nbsp;the north. However, Egypt turned her&nbsp;back on Judah when Babylon attacked Jerusalem (<a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer37:5-Jer37:11\">Jer 37:5–11</a>). •&nbsp;When there was little rain in the fall and spring in Palestine, a summer without rain could destroy crops and cause a food shortage. The food supply also ran out under the prolonged siege of a city (Jan 588–July 586 BC), and many people starved to death (<a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Kgs25:2-2Kgs25:3\">2&nbsp;Kgs 25:2–3</a>; cp. <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer37:21\">Jer 37:21</a>).</p>",
    "associations": {
      "passage": [
        {
          "start_ref": "25001019",
          "start_ref_usfm": "LAM 1:19",
          "end_ref": "25001019",
          "end_ref_usfm": "LAM 1:19"
        }
      ],
      "resource": []
    }
  },
  {
    "content_id": 20006,
    "reference_id": 19174,
    "title": "Lamentations 1:20",
    "media_type": "Text",
    "index_reference": "25001020",
    "language": "eng",
    "content": "<p>The leaders and people of Judah had rebelled (<a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer2:17\">Jer 2:17</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer5:6\">5:6</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer5:23\">23</a>) by rejecting the one true God and his commandments and by resisting the invaders God had sent (<a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Kgs24:1\">2&nbsp;Kgs 24:1</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Kgs24:20\">20</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Chr36:13\">2&nbsp;Chr 36:13</a>).</p>",
    "associations": {
      "passage": [
        {
          "start_ref": "25001020",
          "start_ref_usfm": "LAM 1:20",
          "end_ref": "25001020",
          "end_ref_usfm": "LAM 1:20"
        }
      ],
      "resource": []
    }
  },
  {
    "content_id": 20007,
    "reference_id": 19175,
    "title": "Lamentations 1:21",
    "media_type": "Text",
    "index_reference": "25001021",
    "language": "eng",
    "content": "<p>the day you promised: The poet’s spirit was heartened by the belief that God would set up a day when everyone—oppressors and victims—would be judged justly (see <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa13:6\">Isa 13:6</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa13:9\">9</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer46:10-Jer46:12\">Jer 46:10–12</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer46:27-Jer46:28\">27–28</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Amos5:18-Amos5:20\">Amos 5:18–20</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Obad1:15\">Obad 1:15</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Thess5:2-1Thess5:3\">1&nbsp;Thes 5:2–3</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Thess2:2\">2&nbsp;Thes 2:2</a>).</p>",
    "associations": {
      "passage": [
        {
          "start_ref": "25001021",
          "start_ref_usfm": "LAM 1:21",
          "end_ref": "25001021",
          "end_ref_usfm": "LAM 1:21"
        }
      ],
      "resource": []
    }
  },
  {
    "content_id": 20020,
    "reference_id": 19188,
    "title": "Lamentations 2:1",
    "media_type": "Text",
    "index_reference": "25002001",
    "language": "eng",
    "content": "<p>the heights of heaven: Jerusalem’s buildings were splendid, adorned with precious metals and jewels. Jerusalem had the reputation of being the sacred city of the Lord. •&nbsp;his Temple (literally <em>his footstool</em>): Cp. <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Chr28:2\">1&nbsp;Chr 28:2</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps99:5\">Pss 99:5</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps132:7\">132:7</a>.</p>",
    "associations": {
      "passage": [
        {
          "start_ref": "25002001",
          "start_ref_usfm": "LAM 2:1",
          "end_ref": "25002001",
          "end_ref_usfm": "LAM 2:1"
        }
      ],
      "resource": []
    }
  },
  {
    "content_id": 20014,
    "reference_id": 19182,
    "title": "Lamentations 2:1–22",
    "media_type": "Text",
    "index_reference": "25002001-25002022",
    "language": "eng",
    "content": "<p>This chapter graphically portrays the Lord as Jerusalem’s destroyer.</p>",
    "associations": {
      "passage": [
        {
          "start_ref": "25002001",
          "start_ref_usfm": "LAM 2:1",
          "end_ref": "25002022",
          "end_ref_usfm": "LAM 2:22"
        }
