    }
  },
  {
    "content_id": 20022,
    "reference_id": 19190,
    "title": "Lamentations 2:22",
    "media_type": "Text",
    "index_reference": "25002022",
    "language": "eng",
    "content": "<p>calling them to a day of feasting: The poet compares Jerusalem’s destruction to an invitation to a banquet at which war, famine, wild animals, and sickness would feast on the wicked in Jerusalem (<a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut28:15-Deut28:68\">Deut 28:15–68</a>; cp. <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rev19:17-Rev19:21\">Rev 19:17–21</a>).</p>",
    "associations": {
      "passage": [
        {
          "start_ref": "25002022",
          "start_ref_usfm": "LAM 2:22",
          "end_ref": "25002022",
          "end_ref_usfm": "LAM 2:22"
        }
      ],
      "resource": []
    }
  },
  {
    "content_id": 20028,
    "reference_id": 19196,
    "title": "Lamentations 3:1–24",
    "media_type": "Text",
    "index_reference": "25003001-25003024",
    "language": "eng",
    "content": "<p>The author speaks of the suffering of Judah and Jerusalem as his own.</p>",
    "associations": {
      "passage": [
        {
          "start_ref": "25003001",
          "start_ref_usfm": "LAM 3:1",
          "end_ref": "25003024",
          "end_ref_usfm": "LAM 3:24"
        }
      ],
      "resource": []
    }
  },
  {
    "content_id": 20029,
    "reference_id": 19197,
    "title": "Lamentations 3:1–66",
    "media_type": "Text",
    "index_reference": "25003001-25003066",
    "language": "eng",
    "content": "<p>In this chapter, the author laments what has happened (<a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lam3:1-Lam3:20\">3:1–20</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lam3:48-Lam3:54\">48–54</a>), remembers the faithful love of the Lord (<a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lam3:21-Lam3:25\">3:21–25</a>), describes how God’s people should respond (<a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lam3:26-Lam3:47\">3:26–47</a>), and calls upon the Lord in prayer (<a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lam3:55-Lam3:66\">3:55–66</a>).</p>",
    "associations": {
      "passage": [
        {
          "start_ref": "25003001",
          "start_ref_usfm": "LAM 3:1",
          "end_ref": "25003066",
          "end_ref_usfm": "LAM 3:66"
        }
      ],
      "resource": []
    }
  },
  {
    "content_id": 20046,
    "reference_id": 19214,
    "title": "Lamentations 3:6–9",
    "media_type": "Text",
    "index_reference": "25003006-25003009",
    "language": "eng",
    "content": "<p>Some understand these verses as a poetic reference to Jeremiah’s confinement in a muddy cistern before the destruction of Jerusalem (<a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer38:6-Jer38:13\">Jer 38:6–13</a>).</p>",
    "associations": {
      "passage": [
        {
          "start_ref": "25003006",
          "start_ref_usfm": "LAM 3:6",
          "end_ref": "25003009",
          "end_ref_usfm": "LAM 3:9"
        }
      ],
      "resource": []
    }
  },
  {
    "content_id": 20048,
    "reference_id": 19216,
    "title": "Lamentations 3:9",
    "media_type": "Text",
    "index_reference": "25003009",
    "language": "eng",
    "content": "<p>blocked my way .&nbsp;.&nbsp;. made my road crooked: Sin causes confusion and cuts a person or a community off from a happy future. Innocent people know the future as a straight path that is easy to follow (<a href=\"https://ref.ly/Prov21:8\">Prov 21:8</a>). Isaiah imagined God’s activities as a procession on a straight road that his worshipers would prepare (<a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa40:3\">Isa 40:3</a>).</p>",
    "associations": {
      "passage": [
        {
          "start_ref": "25003009",
          "start_ref_usfm": "LAM 3:9",
          "end_ref": "25003009",
          "end_ref_usfm": "LAM 3:9"
        }
      ],
      "resource": []
    }
  },
  {
    "content_id": 20030,
    "reference_id": 19198,
    "title": "Lamentations 3:12",
    "media_type": "Text",
    "index_reference": "25003012",
    "language": "eng",
    "content": "<p>Compare <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Job6:4\">Job 6:4</a>.</p>",
    "associations": {
      "passage": [
        {
          "start_ref": "25003012",
          "start_ref_usfm": "LAM 3:12",
          "end_ref": "25003012",
          "end_ref_usfm": "LAM 3:12"
        }
      ],
      "resource": []
    }
  },
  {
    "content_id": 20031,
    "reference_id": 19199,
    "title": "Lamentations 3:19",
    "media_type": "Text",
    "index_reference": "25003019",
    "language": "eng",
    "content": "<p>is bitter beyond words (or <em>is wormwood and gall</em>): Wormwood is a plant with a bitter taste; here it represents the emotional intensity of inner agony (<a href=\"https://ref.ly/Prov5:4\">Prov 5:4</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rev8:11\">Rev 8:11</a>). Gall is a poisonous plant that causes severe physical pain if eaten; it is a powerful symbol for extremely stressful emotions (<a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut29:18\">Deut 29:18</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps69:21\">Ps 69:21</a>). The author seems to be at a dead end from which he cannot escape.</p>",
    "associations": {
      "passage": [
        {
          "start_ref": "25003019",
          "start_ref_usfm": "LAM 3:19",
          "end_ref": "25003019",
          "end_ref_usfm": "LAM 3:19"
        }
      ],
      "resource": []
    }
  },
  {
    "content_id": 20033,
    "reference_id": 19201,
    "title": "Lamentations 3:22",
    "media_type": "Text",
    "index_reference": "25003022",
    "language": "eng",
    "content": "<p>The faithful love of the Lord is the basis for the poet’s recovery from deep depression. As with Jeremiah in the cistern (<a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer38:6-Jer38:13\">Jer 38:6–13</a>) and Jonah in the stomach of the great fish (<a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jonah2:2-Jonah2:10\">Jon 2:2–10</a>), the Lord provided salvation from death.</p>",
    "associations": {
      "passage": [
        {
          "start_ref": "25003022",
          "start_ref_usfm": "LAM 3:22",
          "end_ref": "25003022",
          "end_ref_usfm": "LAM 3:22"
        }
      ],
      "resource": []
    }
  },
  {
    "content_id": 20032,
    "reference_id": 19200,
    "title": "Lamentations 3:22–33",
    "media_type": "Text",
    "index_reference": "25003022-25003033",
    "language": "eng",
    "content": "<p>God’s love and faithfulness never cease. Just as God had been faithful in bringing judgment on Jerusalem for their sins, he would be faithful in bringing restoration to those who returned to him.</p>",
    "associations": {
      "passage": [
        {
          "start_ref": "25003022",
          "start_ref_usfm": "LAM 3:22",
          "end_ref": "25003033",
          "end_ref_usfm": "LAM 3:33"
        }
      ],
      "resource": []
    }
  },
  {
    "content_id": 20034,
    "reference_id": 19202,
    "title": "Lamentations 3:23",
    "media_type": "Text",
    "index_reference": "25003023",
    "language": "eng",
    "content": "<p>God’s faithfulness speaks of his absolute reliability, which is evident in his daily mercies. He continually provides a habitable world in which we&nbsp;can live.</p>",
    "associations": {
      "passage": [
        {
          "start_ref": "25003023",
          "start_ref_usfm": "LAM 3:23",
          "end_ref": "25003023",
          "end_ref_usfm": "LAM 3:23"
        }
      ],
      "resource": []
    }
  },
  {
    "content_id": 20035,
    "reference_id": 19203,
    "title": "Lamentations 3:24",
    "media_type": "Text",
    "index_reference": "25003024",
    "language": "eng",
    "content": "<p>The Lord is my inheritance: The land of Canaan had been regarded as Israel’s inheritance since the time of Moses (<a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod15:17\">Exod 15:17</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Josh21:19\">Josh 21:19</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Chr28:8\">1&nbsp;Chr 28:8</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps47:4\">Ps 47:4</a>), but the true inheritance of God’s people is really God himself (see <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps16:5-Ps16:6\">Ps 16:5–6</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Eph1:11\">Eph 1:11</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Heb9:15\">Heb 9:15</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Pet1:3-1Pet1:4\">1&nbsp;Pet 1:3–4</a>).</p>",
    "associations": {
      "passage": [
        {
          "start_ref": "25003024",
          "start_ref_usfm": "LAM 3:24",
          "end_ref": "25003024",
          "end_ref_usfm": "LAM 3:24"
        }
      ],
      "resource": []
    }
  },
  {
    "content_id": 20036,
    "reference_id": 19204,
    "title": "Lamentations 3:26",
    "media_type": "Text",
    "index_reference": "25003026",
    "language": "eng",
    "content": "<p>Those who are confident of God’s plan can wait quietly for him to grant salvation.</p>",
    "associations": {
      "passage": [
        {
          "start_ref": "25003026",
          "start_ref_usfm": "LAM 3:26",
          "end_ref": "25003026",
          "end_ref_usfm": "LAM 3:26"
        }
      ],
      "resource": []
    }
  },
  {
    "content_id": 20037,
    "reference_id": 19205,
    "title": "Lamentations 3:28",
    "media_type": "Text",
    "index_reference": "25003028",
    "language": "eng",
    "content": "<p>sit alone in silence: Humble submission stops the tongue and quiets the heart.</p>",
    "associations": {
      "passage": [
        {
          "start_ref": "25003028",
          "start_ref_usfm": "LAM 3:28",
          "end_ref": "25003028",
          "end_ref_usfm": "LAM 3:28"
        }
      ],
      "resource": []
    }
  },
  {
    "content_id": 20038,
    "reference_id": 19206,
    "title": "Lamentations 3:29–30",
    "media_type": "Text",
    "index_reference": "25003029-25003030",
    "language": "eng",
    "content": "<p>In the ancient Near East, lying face down in the dust expressed submission (<a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen17:1-Gen17:3\">Gen 17:1–3</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lev9:24\">Lev 9:24</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Josh7:6\">Josh 7:6</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Sam5:4\">1&nbsp;Sam 5:4</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Kgs18:39\">1&nbsp;Kgs 18:39</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Chr21:16\">1&nbsp;Chr 21:16</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt17:5-Matt17:6\">Matt 17:5–6</a>). •&nbsp;To turn the other cheek also expresses submission. Jesus evidently had this verse in mind when he taught his disciples to submit to persecution (<a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt5:39\">Matt 5:39</a>). This response recognizes that God is sovereign even over our suffering.</p>",
    "associations": {
      "passage": [
        {
          "start_ref": "25003029",
          "start_ref_usfm": "LAM 3:29",
          "end_ref": "25003030",
          "end_ref_usfm": "LAM 3:30"
        }
      ],
      "resource": []
    }
  },
  {
    "content_id": 20039,
    "reference_id": 19207,
    "title": "Lamentations 3:31",
    "media_type": "Text",
    "index_reference": "25003031",
    "language": "eng",
    "content": "<p>Compare <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps103:8-Ps103:11\">Psalm 103:8–11</a>.</p>",
    "associations": {
      "passage": [
        {
          "start_ref": "25003031",
          "start_ref_usfm": "LAM 3:31",
          "end_ref": "25003031",
          "end_ref_usfm": "LAM 3:31"
        }
      ],
      "resource": []
    }
  },
  {
    "content_id": 20040,
    "reference_id": 19208,
    "title": "Lamentations 3:34–36",
    "media_type": "Text",
    "index_reference": "25003034-25003036",
    "language": "eng",
    "content": "<p>The people of Judah were doing such things before Jerusalem was destroyed (see <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer5:26-Jer5:31\">Jer 5:26–31</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer21:11-Jer21:14\">21:11–14</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer23:10-Jer23:14\">23:10–14</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mic3:1-Mic3:12\">Mic 3</a>).</p>",
    "associations": {
      "passage": [
        {
          "start_ref": "25003034",
          "start_ref_usfm": "LAM 3:34",
          "end_ref": "25003036",
          "end_ref_usfm": "LAM 3:36"
        }
      ],
      "resource": []
    }
  },
  {
    "content_id": 20041,
    "reference_id": 19209,
    "title": "Lamentations 3:37–39",
    "media_type": "Text",
    "index_reference": "25003037-25003039",
    "language": "eng",
    "content": "<p>Some calamities have natural causes (<a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke13:1-Luke13:5\">Luke 13:1–5</a>), and bad things happen to the righteous as well as to the wicked (<a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt5:45\">Matt 5:45</a>); whatever happens, we should give thanks (<a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Thess5:18\">1&nbsp;Thes 5:18</a>) and not complain.</p>",
    "associations": {
      "passage": [
        {
          "start_ref": "25003037",
          "start_ref_usfm": "LAM 3:37",
          "end_ref": "25003039",
          "end_ref_usfm": "LAM 3:39"
        }
      ],
      "resource": []
    }
  },
  {
    "content_id": 20042,
    "reference_id": 19210,
    "title": "Lamentations 3:40–42",
    "media_type": "Text",
    "index_reference": "25003040-25003042",
    "language": "eng",
    "content": "<p>Repentance is the key to receiving salvation (<a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa1:27\">Isa 1:27</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer3:22\">Jer 3:22</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ezek3:21\">Ezek 3:21</a>).</p>",
    "associations": {
      "passage": [
        {
          "start_ref": "25003040",
          "start_ref_usfm": "LAM 3:40",
          "end_ref": "25003042",
          "end_ref_usfm": "LAM 3:42"
        }
      ],
      "resource": []
    }
  },
  {
    "content_id": 20043,
    "reference_id": 19211,
    "title": "Lamentations 3:48–66",
    "media_type": "Text",
    "index_reference": "25003048-25003066",
    "language": "eng",
    "content": "<p>The author focuses on the viciousness of the enemies and cries out to the Lord.</p>",
    "associations": {
      "passage": [
        {
          "start_ref": "25003048",
          "start_ref_usfm": "LAM 3:48",
          "end_ref": "25003066",
          "end_ref_usfm": "LAM 3:66"
        }
      ],
      "resource": []
    }
  },
  {
    "content_id": 20044,
    "reference_id": 19212,
    "title": "Lamentations 3:52–57",
    "media_type": "Text",
    "index_reference": "25003052-25003057",
    "language": "eng",
    "content": "<p>This passage might refer to Jeremiah’s experience in the cistern (<a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer37:11-Jer37:15\">Jer 37:11–15</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer38:1-Jer38:13\">38:1–13</a>).</p>",
    "associations": {
      "passage": [
        {
          "start_ref": "25003052",
          "start_ref_usfm": "LAM 3:52",
          "end_ref": "25003057",
          "end_ref_usfm": "LAM 3:57"
        }
      ],
      "resource": []
    }
  },
  {
    "content_id": 20045,
    "reference_id": 19213,
    "title": "Lamentations 3:58–66",
    "media_type": "Text",
    "index_reference": "25003058-25003066",
    "language": "eng",
    "content": "<p>Jerusalem deserved punishment, but the enemies carried it out with undeserved cruelty. The writer calls upon God to punish them.</p>",
    "associations": {
      "passage": [
        {
          "start_ref": "25003058",
          "start_ref_usfm": "LAM 3:58",
          "end_ref": "25003066",
          "end_ref_usfm": "LAM 3:66"
        }
      ],
      "resource": []
    }
  },
  {
    "content_id": 20047,
    "reference_id": 19215,
    "title": "Lamentations 3:64–66",
    "media_type": "Text",
    "index_reference": "25003064-25003066",
    "language": "eng",
    "content": "<p>This prayer for vengeance is similar to several psalms (see “<span data-bnType=\"resourceReference\" data-resourceId=\"203217\" data-resourceType=\"TyndaleStudyNotesThemes\">Prayers for Vengeance</span>” Theme Note).</p>",
    "associations": {
      "passage": [
        {
          "start_ref": "25003064",
          "start_ref_usfm": "LAM 3:64",
          "end_ref": "25003066",
          "end_ref_usfm": "LAM 3:66"
        }
      ],
      "resource": [
        {
          "reference_id": 203217,
          "content_id": 500274,
          "resource_code": "TyndaleStudyNotesThemes",
          "label": "Prayers for Vengeance",
          "language": "eng"
        }
      ]
    }
  },
  {
    "content_id": 20049,
    "reference_id": 19217,
    "title": "Lamentations 4:1–22",
    "media_type": "Text",
    "index_reference": "25004001-25004022",
    "language": "eng",
    "content": "<p>Although God’s people still experience his judgment, they will soon experience restoration.</p>",
    "associations": {
      "passage": [
        {
          "start_ref": "25004001",
          "start_ref_usfm": "LAM 4:1",
          "end_ref": "25004022",
          "end_ref_usfm": "LAM 4:22"
        }
      ],
      "resource": []
    }
  },
  {
    "content_id": 20056,
    "reference_id": 19224,
    "title": "Lamentations 4:3",
    "media_type": "Text",
    "index_reference": "25004003",
    "language": "eng",
    "content": "<p>like ostriches: See also <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Job39:13-Job39:16\">Job 39:13–16</a>.</p>",
    "associations": {
      "passage": [
        {
          "start_ref": "25004003",
          "start_ref_usfm": "LAM 4:3",
          "end_ref": "25004003",
          "end_ref_usfm": "LAM 4:3"
        }
      ],
      "resource": []
    }
  },
  {
    "content_id": 20057,
    "reference_id": 19225,
    "title": "Lamentations 4:7",
    "media_type": "Text",
    "index_reference": "25004007",
    "language": "eng",
    "content": "<p>like fine jewels: (literally <em>like lapis lazuli</em>): Lapis lazuli is a beautiful blue stone that is soft enough to carve. It is often used in decorations and mosaics.</p>",
    "associations": {
      "passage": [
        {
          "start_ref": "25004007",
          "start_ref_usfm": "LAM 4:7",
          "end_ref": "25004007",
          "end_ref_usfm": "LAM 4:7"
        }
      ],
      "resource": []
    }
  },
  {
    "content_id": 20058,
    "reference_id": 19226,
    "title": "Lamentations 4:8",
    "media_type": "Text",
    "index_reference": "25004008",
    "language": "eng",
    "content": "<p>Skin sticking to bones is symptomatic of the final stages of starvation, just before death.</p>",
    "associations": {
      "passage": [
        {
          "start_ref": "25004008",
          "start_ref_usfm": "LAM 4:8",
          "end_ref": "25004008",
          "end_ref_usfm": "LAM 4:8"
        }
      ],
      "resource": []
    }
  },
  {
    "content_id": 20059,
    "reference_id": 19227,
    "title": "Lamentations 4:9",
    "media_type": "Text",
    "index_reference": "25004009",
    "language": "eng",
    "content": "<p>Long sieges result in a serious lack of food. Even if people could get to the fields, they would find the crops destroyed or harvested to feed the soldiers.</p>",
    "associations": {
      "passage": [
        {
          "start_ref": "25004009",
          "start_ref_usfm": "LAM 4:9",
          "end_ref": "25004009",
          "end_ref_usfm": "LAM 4:9"
        }
      ],
      "resource": []
    }
  },
  {
    "content_id": 20050,
    "reference_id": 19218,
    "title": "Lamentations 4:12",
    "media_type": "Text",
    "index_reference": "25004012",
    "language": "eng",
    "content": "<p>Not a king .&nbsp;.&nbsp;. could march through the gates of Jerusalem: Since God had delivered Jerusalem from Sennacherib of Assyria more than a century earlier (<a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Kgs19:36-2Kgs19:37\">2&nbsp;Kgs 19:36–37</a>), Judeans had strongly believed that not even the mightiest king, Nebuchadnezzar of Babylon, could defeat the city.</p>",
    "associations": {
      "passage": [
        {
          "start_ref": "25004012",
          "start_ref_usfm": "LAM 4:12",
          "end_ref": "25004012",
          "end_ref_usfm": "LAM 4:12"
        }
      ],
      "resource": []
    }
  },
  {
    "content_id": 20051,
    "reference_id": 19219,
    "title": "Lamentations 4:15",
    "media_type": "Text",
    "index_reference": "25004015",
    "language": "eng",
    "content": "<p>It appears that these leaders fled from Jerusalem as refugees to other lands.</p>",
    "associations": {
      "passage": [
        {
          "start_ref": "25004015",
          "start_ref_usfm": "LAM 4:15",
          "end_ref": "25004015",
          "end_ref_usfm": "LAM 4:15"
        }
      ],
      "resource": []
    }
  },
  {
    "content_id": 20052,
    "reference_id": 19220,
    "title": "Lamentations 4:20",
    "media_type": "Text",
    "index_reference": "25004020",
    "language": "eng",
    "content": "<p>Our king .&nbsp;.&nbsp;. was caught: A reference to Zedekiah, who tried to flee but was caught and treated cruelly by Nebuchadnezzar (<a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Kgs25:4-2Kgs25:7\">2&nbsp;Kgs 25:4–7</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer39:4-Jer39:7\">Jer 39:4–7</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer52:9-Jer52:11\">52:9–11</a>).</p>",
    "associations": {
      "passage": [
        {
          "start_ref": "25004020",
